  "text": "In concordance with current theorising, the -entrepreneurial‖ impact of failure outlined in table 3 illustrates that failure can have a seemingly negative impact in terms of self-efficacy and risk-taking propensity. Echoing [CITATION_1] sentiments, further research is required to understand the relationship between losing a business and entrepreneurial self-efficacy. As will be demonstrated subsequently, this is a complex issue and experiencing failure can, at the same time, lead to many positive learning outcomes. This apparent duality is captured succinctly by Tom when he states that: -I still consider it one of the best periods of my life and in some ways one of the worst periods of my life‖.",
